titles.title: Making further continuing appropriations for fiscal year 2012, and for other purposes.

action.text: Mr. Rogers (KY) asked unanimous consent to consider as introduced.
Motion to reconsider laid on the table Agreed to without objection.

vote.text: Received in the Senate, read twice, considered, read the third time, and passed without amendment by Unanimous Consent.

action.text: Message on Senate action sent to the House.

bill.summary: 12/16/2011--Public Law. (This measure has not been amended since it was introduced. The summary of that version is repeated here.) Amends the Continuing Appropriations Act, 2012 (P.L. 112-36) to extend through December 17, 2011, specified continuing appropriations for FY2012.
